Bxd3 18.Qxd3 Bxf4 19.Qf5 $1 { with higher prospects for White after } 19...Bxe3+ 20.fxe3 Qe7 21.e4 $14 ) 8.Qxd8+ Kxd8 9.gxf3 g6 ( { More passive is } 9...Kc7 10.b3 Be7 11.Bb2 Rd8 12.h4 g6 13.Ne4 Nxe4 ( { no better is } 13...Nh5 14.Be5+ Kb6 15.a4 a5 16.Be2 $14 ) 14.fxe4 h5 15.Be5+ ( 15.Be2 $5 ) 15...Bd6 16.Bf6 Re8 17.f3 $14 { with White's pleasant edge, Aronian - Vachier Lagrave, Karlsruhe, 2017. } ) 10.b3 Bg7 11.Bb2 Ke7 ( { Black will hardly do without } 11...b6 $5 { and can play it at once, then a transposition is very likely after } 12.O-O-O+ { , especially if the king is kept in the center rather than } 12...Kc7 13.Ne4 Ne8 14.h4 Bxb2+ 15.Kxb2 $14 ) 12.Bg2 $146 ( { As mentioned, Black is prepared for } 12.Ne4 b6 ) ( { Alternatively, in case of } 12.O-O-O { he can mobilize his army by means of } 12...Be6 ) 12...Rd8 13.Na4 $5 { A different and more promising route for the knight. } 13...b6 14.f4 Bd7 15.O-O-O Rac8 16.Be5 Ne8 17.Nb2 Bxe5 18.fxe5 $14 

